
[1]zarnich

   ZARNICH, n. [See Arsenic.] The name of a genus of fossils, which are
   inflammable, of a plain uniform structure, not flexible or elastic,
   soluble in oil, and burning with a whitish flame and noxious smell like
   garlic. This substance is supposed to be sulphureted aresenic. Of this
   genus there are four species; one the real sandarach; another is sold
   under the name of orpiment.
